spanGrp.span: leng soo, yaapuo soo mwe pwet
one time, there was a man
wan de, wan man i stap
van, mo longbini ka ba ane masólo
he wanted to eat a fish
me van mo dokone san vakten me van lon teh
he went and pulled his canoe to the sea
i go i pulum kenu blong hem i go long solwota
san avaloh, mo dokone vakten me valoh me van
his paddle, he pulled his canoe and paddled on
parel blong hem, i pulum kenu i padel i go
me van lon teh, me van lon moso
he went to the sea, he went to to the clear place (far away)
i go long solwota, i go long aotsaed
mo topne string (wou) me van pwet lon teh
he threw the string out into the sea
i sakem string blong hem i go long solwota
masólo desoo tere mee ka ne saa lan san string (wou)
no fish would come to hang on his string
wan fis i no kam hang long string blong hem
mo pwet, mo pado van, van, mo pado maneot gon, van, yaa mwe keleh, a tere seene masólo desoo
he went on, he went on fishing, he fished till the morning, the sun turned around, no fish
i stap, i huk gogo, i huk long moning nomo, gogo, san i tanem, be i no hukum wan fis
mo nunu san string, me mee, mo topne mo pwet lon vakten
he folded the fishing string, he came and threw it into the canoe
i rolem string blong hem i kam, i sakem i stap long kenu
i prea i go long God
mwe kie, Yaapuo, nam longbini kop sengane masólo desoo mane ngyo
he said, God, I want that you give me some fish
i talem, God, mi wantem yu givim wan fis blong mi
nam pado maneot gon, me mee yaa mwe keleh
I am fishing since this morning, the sun turned around
mi huk long moning nomo, i kam san i tanem
but I did not catch a fish
be mi no hukum wan fis
a nam longbini ko-p sengane masólo desoo mane ngyo
and I want that you give a fish to me
mo mi wantem yu givim wan fis
monok, yaapuo kiye mwe s- laekem (mo toptahe) san wou me van lon teh teteh
that said, that man throw his string into the sea again
finis, man ya i slaekem string blong hem i go long solwota bakagen
me van pwet, mo pwet, mo longtone san string
it went and stayed, he listened to his string
i go stap, i stap lesen long string blong hem
masólo soo me mee, mu gumne string
one fish came and hold the string
wan fis i kam, i holem string
mwe saapwet ne san string, mo dokone, masólo mo dokone
it hung at his string, it pulled, the fish pulled
i hang long string blong hem, i pulum, fis i pulum
mo dokone mee, masólo mo dokone mee van
he pulled the fish towards him, the fish pulled it away
i pulum i kam, fis i pulum i go
mwe tibyakne, masólo kiye mo dokone mane san vakten, me van van van, me van lon moso
he tried hard, that fish pulled his canoe, it went went went far away to the open place
i traem, fis ya i pulum wetem kenu blong hem, i go go go, i go long dip ples
mwe téé me ot, mwe lehe ot soron
he looked to the shore, he saw that the shore was far away
i luk i kam long so, i luk so i longwe
a ngye mwe pwet soron lon moso ke lon moso
and he was far, far away in the open place
be hem i stap longwe aotsaed we aotsaed
mwe tibyakne masólo kiye van van
he tried hard to (to pull) that fish
mo dokone masólo kiye me mee, me mee, mwe lehe masólo kiye ma saapwet lamwiye, mwe lehe me e laasi masólo
he pulled that fish closer, closer, he saw that fish floating on topi, he saw that it was a giant of a fish
i pulum fis ya i kam, i kam, i luk fis ya i flot i stap antap, hem i luk i wan bigfela fis
mwe lehe masólo kiye welen me nek ne
he looked at that fish, he was afraid of it
i luk fis ya, i fraet long hem
mu nunu monok, mo topne lon vakten, me valoh me mee ot
after he rolled up his string, he threw it into the canoe, and paddled to the shore
i rolem finis, i sakem long kenu, i padel i kam so
momane lonlakele, vanten ke tobo (vanten lam pwee) lam kie ka
So today, many people say that
olsem long taem naoia, fulap man oli talem se
lam longbini tiri desoo, lam wisine Yaapuo
they want something, they ask it from God
oli wantem wan samting, oli askem long God
lam kie Yaapuo, ko-p kuone ngyo
they say, God, you should help me
oli talem, God i helpem mi
nam longbini ko-p sengane tiri desoo mane ngyo
I want that you give something to me
mi wantem yu givim samting long mi
ka Yaapuo te sengane te mee, et dam mwisyene.
when God gives and it comes, we dislike it
taem God i givim i kam, be yumi no wantem
mu wisi yaapuo mwe sengane masólo mee monok, a ngye mo mwisyene
he asked God that he send a fish, but he disliked it
i askem god i givim fis i kam finis, be hem i no wantem
kiye gon me gie punen, sipa
emya nao en blong story, sipa
